values:
i went last night to a concert at appleton west high school.  it was like a battle of the band thing.  you were supposed to have a student i.d. to get in, but they didn't check.  anyways. the bands really sucked so we left.  we hung out at barnes and noble and the guy behind the counter hit on erin.  she liked it.  when i got home i ate some cookie dough.  the container cut my hand.  then i went to bed.  

i'm kinda in a crabby mood today.  maybe its because i have to do homework, maybe it's your fault.

i just get really tired of school sometimes. 




ok most of the time.

i'm sitting here in the hotel computer desk in charleston, south carolina.  prettty sweet eh?  well i'm bored cause it's sunday night and nothing is open so we decided to just go back to the hotel.  i have had a very full day today.  this morning we woke up and went downtown and walked the battery.  awesomely huge houses.  then we had lunch at bubba gumps.  i ate soooo much shrimp.  whatev.  then we went shopping...good times.  then we drove to the beach.  oh the beach.  it was so cold, but emily and i still put our feet in the ocean.  go us!  then we came back to the hotel.  on saturday we visited charleston southern university where i have recently been accepted.  i don't know if i will go there.  but it was a good experience none the less.  

i miss all of my friends severely and i'm glad to be coming home tomorrow.  however, i haven't done any of my math homework yet and so i'm very nervous about getting it done and understanding it.  

well i'm going to go back to the room now.  so i hope to see/hear from everyone soon!

so i would just like to post my compliant.  i went to donate blood today.  i got my finger pricked.  i filled out all the forms, and then i waited and hour and half.  so then when i finally got to the lady that sticks the needle in you, she told me my veins were too small.  yeah.  


whatever.

so i'm sitting here in my brother's dorm room.  yeah nothing much is happening, no one is around cause it's a friday night.  but hey i'm with my brother so i'm having fun! um lets see.  today i had a tour of bethel.  it was ok.  nothing special.  if charleston doesn't work out it wouldn't be the death of me go there.  
but yeah so i'm going to go now cause there is nothing to do.  haha.  so have an awesome night and find something cool to do.  like hang out with your brother...
do people realize that words can really hurt? sometimes i wonder how people can say such hurtful words.  and its not even that they can say them to your face either.

alright so there has been alot going on lately and i haven't had much time to write it all down.  school has been crazy leaving me with homework everyday.  cheerleading has been going really well, we've been having practice five days a week in order to get ready for homecoming.  its going to be awesome and anyone that has the chance should stop by atleast for half time.  

big news! i was nominated for homecoming court! how weird is that! i honestly doubt it will go any further then just being nominated but i guess we'll see.  i really am just honored to have been nominated, and thats enough for me.

i'm really excited to go rolling! yeah man! oh and if anyone messes with my house they are getting it back ten fold!

i'm going to a switchfoot concert on the 21st in chitown and i'm so stoked! oh man!

so lately i have been figuring out who my real friends are.  its weird how everybody knows you are in a fight with someone when you didn't even know it yourself.  hmmm. well anyways, i don't have much time with school and work and cheerleading to hang out with my friends but when i do, i just let them down anyways.  i can't make everybody happy and that sucks.  i just want everybody to enjoy themselves.  sigh.




i don't worry about the things i can't control.  i worry about messing up the things i have to control.

so i was late last night coming home, and my dad wanted up for me. now mind you i was only like ten minutes late, but apparently we are "talking about my consequences today" sigh.....

so i had kinda a crappy weeked. but i don't want to bog you down with all the nasty details....

hey for anyone who cares! david is coming from colorado over homecoming weekend! i'm so stoked! he's going to come to the homecoming football game and such craziness!  it's gonna be awesome!

but i have to go now cause i have about six billion things i have to do and not enough time to do it all!

i hate how people, and by people i mean old people, are all like "i wish i could go back to high school" i def think that i'm going to be happy to be done with high school.  i hate having to make everyone happy.  but the truth is i really really honestly with all my heart want everyone to be happy.  








p.s. kids applying to college is sweet! i highly recommend it!

i have been so busy lately....my goodness. i thought then when school started it might slow down, but i'm pretty convinced that it made things crazier.  

ok well lets see lately i have been doing some cheerleading practice like normal.  and last night erin harris and i made our usual ben and jerry's run. but this time we brought some friends along.  i think we should start a ben and jerry's eating club so that i can eat ben all the time.  sigh. when i told this guy that i had ate ice cream he asked me if that was healthy for a cheerleader to be doing.  he's like "aren't you gonna get fat from eating that kind of stuff?" i was so upset.  hey whatever, i do what i want. 

i saw an all american rejects music video and i had forgotten how hot the leader singer was.  he has the bluest eyes i have ever seen.    

friday there is a home game so i expect everyone within driving distance to come! ok!?!?!? 

have you ever wanted to just tell everyone exactly what you think of them?  cause like seriously, i notice everything about everyone.  if i have seen them, i have analyzed everything about them.  sometimes i just wonder why people are the way they are.  then i remember, people probably don't understand me any better then i understand them. 

haha.

so i was wondering....do people realize it when you really like them?  you know the kind of like where you just want him to know but you're too scared to tell him.  you just hope that by some telopathic phenomenom he would just know.  you know what i mean those awkward conversations where you're just trying not to burst out and tell him everything you think but you don't want to look like a fool.  maybe i'm the only one who thinks this way. maybe i'm crazy.  i just don't know anymore.  i'm tired of trying to figure out what is normal and what is psychopathic.  so i'm just going to pretend like i don't know the difference and continue in my silence.....sigh i hate high school......it sucks the big one....


isn't it funny how three days later i can be so upset again.  what is that all about anyways...

so everybody has been freaking out about finding a date and a dress for homecoming for like weeks now.  and to tell you the truth i was caught up in it too.  i was so worried that i would have to go with my friends(wouldn't that be horrible).

but now i have realized that well, if i don't get the "perfect dress" and the "perfect date" i will still have a good time.   hey even i don't get a date at all i think i will still have a good time.  i mean don't get me wrong there are plenty of guys i would be more then thrilled to go with to homecoming, i'm just not going to impress them anymore.  basically i'm not going to try to be anyone that i'm not.  i'm just going to be myself and not worry about what people think or say about me.  just be myself again...if i remember how to do that...i guess we'll see what happens....

so anyways....just so you all know....

going nowhere, going nowhere
their tears are filling up their glasses
no expression, no expression
hide my head i want to drown my sorrow

are the best i've ever had

if anyone here has not seen donnie darko, get on it.......



oh and just so you all don't think i'm all depressed or something....i just like this song cause it's in donnie.....don't worry about me, really.

alrighty so hear is the scoop poop.....aka my schedule

1.)ceramics and sculpture 3
2.)ap calculus
3.)homeroom....duh
4.)espanol 4....ole
5.)writer's workshop
lunch.....i have like no one in my lunch....sadness is mine
6.)human physiology
7.)study hall/senior release...oh baby oh baby
8.)ap psychology

ewwwww school.

alright so as far as the fall out boy concert went....i didn't.  it was my sister's birthday party so i stayed home when melissa and jessie went.  and just as chessie predicted, they didn't get in.  oh well i guess it happens that way sometimes.
so then the first football game was friday.  all in all it went pretty well.....still things could have gone smoother.  but yeah.  the next home game is on the 10th, so i expect to see all of you that live in fondy to be there.
so anyways, i found this guy in the yearbook that i have never-ever seen or met before.  melissa and jessie know him so we'll see where that goes...he's absolutely adorable, and apparently he has a personality to match.  we'll see....

i've been sooooo busy lately i don't even know what i've been doing. lets see....i've had cheerleading practice every day....then i've been working....and running errands like a crazy woman...and then we had lia's birthday party...yeah that was fun.  um and today i went to uwgb, thats a pretty nice school.  i still don't think i want to stay in wisconsin, but for anyone who is looking at the uw system, i highly recommend it. 

oh my gosh! FALL OUT BOY IS COMING TO APPLETON!!! I'M SOOOOOOO PUMPED!!! they are playing at hollister, which is really weird, but its free!!!!! i'm sooo pumped!!!! 

number one fan concert in oshkosh on the 28th!!!!!!!! woooooohooooo!!!!!!!

so i've sitting here at my house thinking about this summer and all the things i have done, not done, and wished to have done.  three things that did not get accomplished...1)80s nite with jessie...2)any of the things lisa, lia, kristy, and i wrote down to do....and 3)visiting my good friend elizabeth in tennessee.
but yeah so i suppose there still is two weeks left to do these things....

so there are some pretty creepy people out there in this little town i like to call home. to anyone who hears what i'm saying..."holla"
but anyways i just got back from camp and it was...in the words of my new friend dave "amazing" but yes it was way more fun then i thought it would be. it was also a whole lot colder then i thought it would be.  oh well.
i have cheerleading pictures tomorrow and i have no idea what to wear.  wait that's right i'm suppose to wear my uniform.....heheh
oh man i'm in such a hyper mood right now i'm like bouncing off the walls.  i bet that when i go back to read this i'm gonna be like "what was i smoking?" i don't know what gets into me sometimes.

yeah so i just got back from cheerleading camp! and it was more awesome then i could have possibly imagined!!! i lost my voice and got picked to try out for there team they send to australia!!! i'm so pumped!!!!
i have funny tan lines on my wrist from the tape.....its bugging me big time....

5-6-7-8-call me!

that's right my squishy friends, i'm going to camp...again.  atleast this time i won't be gone so very long.  just three days then i'll be back.  but then i leave again....for camp...haha you would think that's all i ever do. 

hey awesome news!  we had cheerleading practice today (it was three hours long! we had to do some major touch ups before we went to camp)  and our coaches announced that aimee and i were going to be the squad captains!!! yay!! so anyways that was my exciting news for the week! image, me a varsity cheerleading captain?!?!?!? crazy isn't it.

i spent like two hours today running around shopping for cheerleading camp.  and now i'm at home and i'm spending all my time doing laundry and packing.  i hope i don't forget anything...i have so much to do and remember.   

my sister went shopping with me today.  she told me about how she found a baby squirrel in our driveway.  so my mom and she took it to the humane society so they could take care of it.  i was all upset cause i have always wanted a pet squirrel! would that not be the coolest pet to have!  oh well, maybe next time....

i have no idea why i am in such a good mood. i love it so much!
oh just for all your information japan is it's own country....and its in asia.
oh so awesomely good news! so yesterday my sister called me on melissa's cell phone to tell me that she won the gavin degraw signed poster and t-shirt from sam goody! and that she was going to give it to me since she didn't know who that was! i was pumped! i never win anything....i mean i guess i still haven't won anything but it feels like i have...
well nothing else to say.....so untill tomorrow!

oh my goodness, 
this week has been soooo stinkin crazy! between cheerleading and work, babysitting and drving my sister to oshkosh, i don't have any time to spend just sitting.  except for this 30 seconds i have before i have to go to work.
i miss everybody soo much from camp and when i get a spare second i promise i will email all of you!
cheerleading camp is next week.  almost everybody knows the dance and knows it well, almost everybody. but i won't tell you how i really feel about that. 
i bought the skillet cd yesterday while i was in oshkosh. (by the way, eaa traffic is soooo terrible! if you can avoid it, i highly recommend not going to oshkosh) anywho, yeah i was in a harder rock mood so i went to basic books and i was like, "ooo skillet!" so i bought it. i guess you could say i am an inpulse shopper.  is that such a bad thing? 
ok well i have to go to work, but if you have a minute, pray for me to have strength and energy this week....i need it big time......

alrighty.....
so i just got home from an awesome week at camp! yay! it's sad though cause it was my last year. i'm seriously considering going to work there this next summer however.....

um thats about all that has been going on...if ya wanna know specific stories then you'll have to talk to me!

so here's the dealio.  jessie got her wisdom teeth out today....and she's fine....i mean thats great for her and everything but how is that fair!?!?!?! whatever.....

ya know what else is sad....the number one fan signatures on my arm are almost invisible....tear....i'm just going to have to go to there show in august and get them to sign my arm again.....

camp starts on saturday and i'm so pumped cause i get to see mary mo and lisa! hooray!

just to let you all know.....i'm going to marry pete from fall out boy...sigh..na i'm just playin....but ya'll should check out the latest addition of alternative press....fall out boy on the cover baby! oh yeah you know what i'm talking about....

well i just had an incredibly long week of family and concerts.  lifest was the man like always.  i met some cool people and got to hang out with my friend chessie.  then all my relatives came for the reunion....yeah family.... you know how that goes....but anyway i just dropped off chessie at the airport.  sadness. thats ok it was a fun week.  
i met this kid named russell at lifest.  he was from milwaukee.  pretty nice kid.  
saturday i leave for camp which is cool except i haven't done any of my laundry yet.  yikes.  
oh my gosh! i was so sad to find out that one of my all time favorite stores, weathervane, is going out of business.  ::tear:: i don't know what i'm going to do....

oh my god. i don't think i have ever been this tired.  cheerleading practice started and as it turned out....i'm out of shape! haha go figure! i already took a two hour nap and i and considering taking a second one.  
on a funner note...chessie comes tomorrow! yay! and lifest starts on thursday! yay! i'm so pumped!
i just bought the ugliest shoes that i have ever seen.  i don't know what i'm going to do.

well this is my first entry....yeah i don't really know what to write about but that's cool i guess.  i'm sure when something actually happens this will be way more interesting to read.

definately more to come....
